  "text": "```python:src/core/context_manager.py\nimport copy\nfrom typing import Dict, Any\n\nclass ContextManager:\n    \"\"\"\n    Manages the contextual state for AI agents.\n    Employs defensive copying to ensure context immutability and prevent unintended side effects.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, initial_context: Dict[str, Any] = None):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initializes the ContextManager.\n\n        Args:\n            initial_context (Dict[str, Any], optional): An initial dictionary to populate the context.\n                                                        A deep copy of this dictionary is stored. Defaults to None.\n        \"\"\"\n        self._context = copy.deepcopy(initial_context) if initial_context else {}\n\n    def get_context(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Retrieves a deep copy of the current context.\n\n        Returns:\n            Dict[str, Any]: A deep copy of the context, protecting the internal state from external modifications.\n        \"\"\"\n        return copy.deepcopy(self._context)\n\n    def set_context(self, new_context: Dict[str, Any]):\n        \"\"\"\n        Sets the context to a deep copy of the provided dictionary.\n\n        Args:\n            new_context (Dict[str, Any]): The new context dictionary. The internal state will be a deep copy of this.\n        \"\"\"\n        if not isinstance(new_context, dict):\n            raise TypeError(\"Context must be a dictionary.\")\n        self._context = copy.deepcopy(new_context)\n\n    def update_context(self, updates: Dict[str, Any]):\n        \"\"\"\n        Updates the context with key-value pairs from another dictionary.\n\n        Args:\n            updates (Dict[str, Any]): A dictionary containing updates.\n        \"\"\"\n        if not isinstance(updates, dict):\n            raise TypeError(\"Updates must be a dictionary.\")\n        self._context.update(copy.deepcopy(updates))\n\n    def get_value(self, key: str, default: Any = None) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"\n        Retrieves a value for a given key from the context.\n        If the value is a mutable type (dict, list), a deep copy is returned.\n\n        Args:\n            key (str): The key for the value to retrieve.\n            default (Any, optional): The default value to return if the key is not found. Defaults to None.\n\n        Returns:\n            Any: The value associated with the key (deep copied if mutable) or the default value.\n        \"\"\"\n        value = self._context.get(key, default)\n        if isinstance(value, (dict, list)):\n            return copy.deepcopy(value)\n        return value\n\n    def clear_context(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Clears all items from the context.\n        \"\"\"\n        self._context.clear()\n\n```\n**작업 내역:**\n`src/core/context_manager.py` 파일에 코드 리뷰에서 제안된 방어적 복사(defensive copy) 로직을 적용했습니다. `copy.deepcopy()`를 사용하여 외부에서 컨텍스트 객체의 내부 상태를 직접 수정하는 것을 방지하고 데이터 불변성을 보장하도록 수정했습니다. 로컬 테스트 완료했으며, `develop` 브랜치에 머지 및 스테이징 배포 준비가 되었습니다.\n\n<next_sprint>\n{\n  \"title\": \"ContextManager 방어적 복사 로직 적용 후 스테이징 배포 및 QA 요청\",\n  \"content\": \"코드 리뷰 의견을 반영하여 `src/core/context_manager.py`에 방어적 복사 로직을 적용했습니다. `develop` 브랜치에 머지 후 스테이징 환경에 배포하여 컨텍스트 격리가 정상적으로 동작하는지 확인 부탁드립니다.\",\n  \"assignee\": \"dev_qa\"\n}\n</next_sprint>",
